The Federal Reserve Bank of the United States, the European Central Bank and the British, Swiss and Canadian central banks have decided to fight together the financial market crisis.
More than one hundred billion dollars will be placed in the money markets through auctions.
Banks will have to sell, through an auction system, the interest rates at which they are willing to borrow money.
