In Havana, tall buildings grew and cars, belonging to the cult symbols of the 50's of the last century, circulated on the wide boulevards.
Ernest Hemingway bought a property in San Francisco de Paula, near Havana, and in Cojamar he had his yacht.
Show business stars and politicians across America left their signatures on the walls of the Bodeguita del Medio.
