One of the most picturesque corners of Cuba is the Viàles Valley on the west side of the island.
Exuberant vegetation grows there on calcareous soil.
Mogotes, calcareous balloons, and rocks rise in candlelight from the bottom of the valley, and, from the fertile earth being caught in their bowels, even its rotten rocks are covered with a very dense vegetal carpet.
The valley is where the best quality Cuban tobacco is probably grown.
You can meet the final shape of this product if you visit one of Havana’s cigar factories.
Someone might also find it interesting that this is where the Chilean episode of Major Zeman was shot.
Trinidad
An ancient city founded shortly after the Spanish colonized the island.
It was the slave trade and the sugar trade that brought him fame and wealth.
The richness was embodied in the beauty and the city-window character of this small city.
Koloni-ln-e-pan-lsk-architektura,v-razn-e-ovlivn-n-e-pozd-j-mi francouzsk-mi osadn-ky, se za ty-i stalet-e-tém-nose-m-nila.
Trinidad, located between the sea and the Escambray mountain range, is such a remote place that even in the 50's of the last century, there was no road that would connect this region with the rest of the country.
This isolation allowed him to stay on the sidelines.
We didn’t build anything, and that’s why we didn’t demolish anything either, everyone just had a roof over their head.
