The representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the effort made by members and senators to negotiate and provide the best possible regulation to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the activities of the organizations in order to make the markets work effectively.
Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Law, involves the modernization of financial markets, at a time when it strengthens investor protection, enhances the powers of the leaders of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the different leaders of the European Union.
The new regulation will allow financial advisory services to be provided to both specialized corporate entities and individuals or legal entities, and creates a new type of financial services (ESIS), financial advisory companies (AFIs), which merge with securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it increases the number of systems for the execution of trades in financial instruments, so that it is possible to add to regulated secondary markets multilateral trading systems and order internationalization systems, which compete with current stock exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment services firms to disclose on the market information on key aspects of its business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all transactions they carry out, to facilitate control by the CNMV.
