What insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible claims, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, gender, the age of the driver's license, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
They are that, escoger el seguro de autom vil adecuado es incluso mes diff cil que elegir el modelo de veh culo.
And that is, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in exchange it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the driving licence, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rating to be paid.
It is for this reason that people over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower claim rate due to their prudence.
Similarly, using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the probability of having an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will explain the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various disadvantages when entering into a contract with insurance at an affordable price, as may be the low driving experience and seniority of the driver’s license.
Although the ideal way to be well insured is an insurance at all risks, other more economical options exist.
The most prospective drivers can opt for all-risk insurance with deductible, so that they get the coverage of an insurance at all risk but at a more accessible price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays a part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount will be," said Luis Noguera, Spain manager of First Europa, an online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fires and loss of the vehicle.
One piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25, try to be careful and avoid claims as much as possible, since this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the company owns.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
“The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the company’s profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses," clarifies Noguera.
Beyond the age of 25 it becomes easier for drivers to enter into a contract with insurance, since the claim rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is best to choose all-risk insurance with deductible.
“Normally young people cannot benefit from the experience they have acquired after an accident,” says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once past the ‘fear of the novice’.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable that he negotiate insurance at any risk, as long as his economic situation allows it.
Child marriages are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest claim rate, because the surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be an all-risk insurance with deductible (may be 300 euros), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
“They have a more relaxed drive and they have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchises,” Noguera said.
For retirees, a risk insurance with deductible is preferable (being this one of 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us best according to our personal situation.
